WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:04.000
Downloaded From www.AllSubs.org

00:08.200 --> 00:09.600
Welcome back, Seattle.

00:09.800 --> 00:11.600
Thank you for joining us
in celebrating this,

00:11.900 --> 00:14.200
our 2000th show.

00:14.500 --> 00:17.200
- Hard to believe, isn't it, Roz?
- No, that feels just about right.

00:17.500 --> 00:20.800
Ah, yes, well,
what a festive day this is.

00:21.200 --> 00:23.500
No stop has been unpulled.

00:23.700 --> 00:25.400
I would like to take this opportunity

00:25.600 --> 00:27.900
to acknowledge
the anniversary luncheon spread

00:28.200 --> 00:31.300
provided by our friends
at Señor José Phong,

00:31.700 --> 00:33.600
home of the sweet and sour taco.

00:33.900 --> 00:35.400
And don't forget, a little later,

00:35.700 --> 00:40.000
we'll have Microsoft Chairman
Bill Gates live in studio

00:40.300 --> 00:42.700
to congratulate me on
my 2000th show.

00:43.000 --> 00:44.900
Apparently, I hear through
the grapevine,

00:45.100 --> 00:47.300
he is a big fan.

00:47.600 --> 00:48.800
[LAUGHS]

00:49.000 --> 00:50.400
Roz, what do we have next?

00:50.600 --> 00:52.200
It's time for another blooper.

00:52.500 --> 00:55.800
Oh, well, I believe we're up
to number four

00:56.100 --> 00:59.300
as voted by you, the listeners.

00:59.700 --> 01:02.900
Here's what happened
when a certain producer

01:03.200 --> 01:07.400
didn't realise her microphone
was on during the show.

01:07.800 --> 01:08.800
[LAUGHS]

01:09.100 --> 01:10.900
ROZ [ON RADIO]:
<i>Now what the</i> **** <i>is this?</i>

01:11.100 --> 01:13.000
<i>You call this a</i> ******* <i>paycheque?</i>

01:13.200 --> 01:15.600
<i>How the</i> ****
<i>am I supposed to live on this</i> ****<i>?</i>

01:15.900 --> 01:18.900
<i>I'm gonna have a little word with that</i>
***<i>damn station manager</i>

01:19.200 --> 01:22.400
<i>walking around here like</i>
<i>he owns the mother</i>****<i>ing place.</i>

01:22.700 --> 01:24.400
I can't believe
that wasn't voted number one.

01:24.700 --> 01:28.100
Oh, ha, ladies and gentlemen,
it's our station manager,

01:28.500 --> 01:31.400
KACL's own Kenny Daly. Ha, ha.

01:31.700 --> 01:34.500
Listen, doc, I got a special someone
out there who'd like to say hello.

01:34.800 --> 01:37.100
By all means,
let's bring him in, Kenny.

01:37.300 --> 01:40.900
Ladies and gentlemen,
our special guest has finally arrived.

01:41.200 --> 01:42.200
Please welcome...

01:42.400 --> 01:43.500
[BARKS]

01:43.800 --> 01:44.800
[AIRHORN BLOWS]

01:45.000 --> 01:47.500
- Bulldog?
- Great to see you, doc. Hey, Roz.

01:47.900 --> 01:49.400
FRASIER:
Well, ladies and gentlemen,

01:49.600 --> 01:52.300
it's our old friend and former colleague,
Bob "Bulldog" Briscoe.

01:52.700 --> 01:54.800
Thanks for coming
to celebrate my 2000th show.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.800
Yeah, yeah, congrats.
Didn't think you'd last two weeks.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
Listen up, sports fans, Bulldog here.

02:00.200 --> 02:02.800
I know what you're all thinking:
Bulldog's been gone too long.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.300
How can you get me back on the air?
Okay, listen up.

02:05.600 --> 02:08.199
You send your cards and letters
of support to Kenny Daly, KACL...

02:08.500 --> 02:11.200
Hold on, hold on, Bulldog!
Our special guest has arrived.

02:11.400 --> 02:12.900
- P.O. Box 451, Seattle...
- Bulldog!

02:13.200 --> 02:15.600
Would you and your noisemaker
please wait in Roz's booth?

02:15.900 --> 02:17.800
- This is an air horn, doc.
- Yes, I was referring

02:18.100 --> 02:20.500
to that flapping hole above your chin.
Now get out!

02:23.100 --> 02:24.700
Ladies and gentlemen,
let's please welcome

02:25.000 --> 02:26.500
Microsoft Chairman, Bill Gates.

02:26.700 --> 02:28.200
Ha, ha. Good to see you, sir.

02:28.400 --> 02:30.100
- Sorry I was late.
- Oh, that's all right.

02:30.400 --> 02:33.200
- I was just talking to an old friend.
- Yes, ha, ha.

02:37.400 --> 02:40.300
Well, I've... I've got
so many questions to ask you.

02:40.500 --> 02:43.100
Uh, why don't we just dive right in?

02:43.400 --> 02:44.900
I've been wondering,

02:45.100 --> 02:48.600
when did you first
become a fan of my show?

02:49.000 --> 02:51.800
Excuse me.
Warren from Kirkland is on Line 2.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.500
Ye... Yes, Roz. I won't be taking
any calls until after Mr. Gates has left.

02:56.100 --> 02:59.100
- Actually, it's for Mr. Gates.
FRASIER: Well, um...

02:59.900 --> 03:02.200
Go ahead, caller.
You're on with Mister Bill Gates.

03:02.500 --> 03:04.300
WARREN [ON PHONE]:
<i>Yeah, hi, Mr. Gates.</i>

03:04.600 --> 03:06.200
<i>I bought your new</i>
<i>Windows XP programme,</i>

03:06.500 --> 03:08.800
<i>and I'm about to instal it,</i>
<i>but it's an upgrade.</i>

03:09.000 --> 03:12.000
- <i>Do I need to make a boot disc?</i>
- That's a very good question.

03:12.300 --> 03:14.200
You don't need to make a boot disk.

03:14.500 --> 03:16.200
You just put the CD in,
and it'll upgrade.

03:16.500 --> 03:17.800
I hope that answers your question.

03:18.100 --> 03:21.000
That's a feature of XP,
very quick, very smooth.

03:21.300 --> 03:22.800
- Hey, this is fun.
FRASIER: Ah.

03:24.400 --> 03:26.300
Thank you for calling, Warren.

03:26.600 --> 03:27.700
Now, where were we?

03:28.000 --> 03:31.900
Can Mr. Gates take a few more calls?
The board is lighting up. Wow.

03:32.300 --> 03:34.600
Who knew we had a Line 7?

03:34.900 --> 03:36.800
Uh, Roz, I believe Mr. Gates
is probably anxious

03:37.000 --> 03:40.100
- to get on with the interview.
- No, no, I'm... I'm happy to.

03:40.500 --> 03:42.500
Very well.

03:45.000 --> 03:46.200
Go ahead, caller.

03:46.800 --> 03:49.000
WOMAN CALLER [ON PHONE]:
<i>Wow, Bill Gates. This is so cool.</i>

03:49.300 --> 03:50.300
Thank you.

03:50.500 --> 03:52.300
WOMAN CALLER [ON PHONE]:
<i>Hey, I have a question</i>

03:52.600 --> 03:55.300
<i>about Multilingual User Interface</i>
<i>add-ons. What are those?</i>

03:55.500 --> 03:57.300
BILL:
Well, the Multilingual add-ons

03:57.600 --> 04:01.000
let you run Windows in different
languages. You can use it in German...

04:01.400 --> 04:03.800
Do you believe this
egomaniacal gasbag?

04:04.000 --> 04:05.500
He's taking over my show.

04:05.600 --> 04:07.700
Don't you think
you're exaggerating just a bit?

04:08.000 --> 04:09.600
Who do we have next, Roz?

04:09.900 --> 04:12.500
We have Bob from Fremont.
He has a question about his laptop.

04:12.800 --> 04:14.100
Go ahead, Bob.

04:14.300 --> 04:16.200
I'm listening.

04:24.900 --> 04:26.900
[SIGHS]

04:33.100 --> 04:34.500
[CHUCKLES]

04:34.700 --> 04:38.700
Two thousand shows, ha-ha-ha.

